[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Fraser valley (British Columbia) banner.jpg"],["caption=Farms and the Fraser River near Agassiz, BC"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"'''","value":["The Fraser Valley"]}," is agricultural region of the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Lower Mainland"]]}," of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["British Columbia"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Canada"]]},".  It is gradually being transformed into suburbs of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Vancouver"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Cities"]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Langley (British Columbia)"],["Langley"]]}," - an agricultural town that is becoming a suburb of Vancouver. The Greater Vancouver Zoo is here, as well as Fort Langley, the site of the province's founding."]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Abbotsford"]]}," - a major regional town with a significant commercial airport, and a hub of agriculture. "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Maple Ridge"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Pitt Meadows"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mission (British Columbia)"],["Mission"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Dewdney"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kent (British Columbia)"],["Kent"]]}," along the north bank of the Fraser River."]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Chilliwack"]]}," - where the Fraser River emerges from the mountains"]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Harrison Hot Springs"]]}," - a pretty vacation area next to the mountains"]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Hope (British Columbia)"],["Hope"]]}," - gateway to British Columbia's interior and entrance to the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Lower Mainland"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Other destinations"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Cultus Lake"]}," near ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Chilliwack"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Lindell Beach"]]}," - on Cultus Lake"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Chilliwack Lake"]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\nThe ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Fraser Valley"]]}," has lush fertile farmland, which contributes a large portion of the local produce. The Fraser is also the world's greatest salmon producing river, and a focus for the region's economy, transportation and culture. The towns of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Pitt Meadows"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Maple Ridge"]]},", and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Langley (British Columbia)"],["Langley"]]}," are transforming from agricultural to suburb. ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Abbotsford"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mission (British Columbia)"],["Mission"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Chilliwack"]]},", and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hope (British Columbia)"],["Hope"]]}," remain closer to their agricultural roots, but are also transforming.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Talk"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Wine tasting"]},": Though it isn't quite the viniculture hotbed that the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Okanagan"]]}," is, there are a number of wineries in the Fraser Valley. See ",{"type":"'''","value":["Domaine de Chaberton Estate"]},", which started it all, and ",{"type":"'''","value":["Township 7 Vineyards & Winery"]},", ",{"type":"'''","value":["Glenugie Winery"]},", and ",{"type":"'''","value":["Blackwood Lane Vineyards & Winery"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Langley (British Columbia)#Do"],["Langley"]]},"; ",{"type":"'''","value":["The Fort Wine Company"]}," in historic ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Fort Langley#Do"],["Fort Langley"]]},"; ",{"type":"'''","value":["Blossom Winery"]}," (famous for ice wine and fruit wines) and ",{"type":"'''","value":["Sanduz Estate Wines"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Richmond (British Columbia)#Do"],["Richmond"]]},"; ",{"type":"'''","value":["River's Bend Winery"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Surrey (British Columbia)#Do"],["Surrey"]]},"; ",{"type":"'''","value":["Lotusland Vineyards"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Abbotsford#Do"],["Abbotsford"]]},"; ",{"type":"'''","value":["Blue Heron Winery"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Pitt Meadows#Do"],["Pitt Meadows"]]},"; and ",{"type":"'''","value":["Kermode Wild Berry Winery"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Dewdney"]]},"; ",{"type":"'''","value":["Westham Island Estate Winery"]}," and ",{"type":"'''","value":["Wellbrook Winery"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Delta (British Columbia)"],["Delta"]]},"; and ",{"type":"'''","value":["St. Urban Winery"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Chilliwack"]]},". Look for the handy ",{"type":"'''","value":["Wine Map"]}," from the Fraser Valley Wine Association",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.fvwa.ca\/"]},".  Consider visiting only three to five wineries in a day, to give yourself time to enjoy the visit, available at most of these wineries.  Many wineries will limit you to only three to five wine samples in one visit. Some may charge you a couple of dollars for the tasting, which might be waived if you purchase some wine."]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Pottery"]},": The Fraser Valley Potters Guild",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/members.shaw.ca\/fraservalleypotters\/index_2.htm"]}," has  a handy brochure listing area potters open to tours. Try ",{"type":"'''","value":["Simpson Pottery"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Langley (British Columbia)"],["Aldergrove"]]},"; ",{"type":"'''","value":["Venema Pottery"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Abbotsford"]]},"; ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/jopriestley.com Jo Priestly"]}]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mission (British Columbia)"],["Mission"]]},"; ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.rainforestpottery.com\/ Rainforest Pottery"]}]},", ",{"type":"'''","value":["Schellenberg Pottery"]},", and ",{"type":"'''","value":["Driediger Pottery"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Yarrow"]]},"; ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.greendalepottery.com\/ Greendale Pottery"]}]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Chilliwack"]]},"; and ",{"type":"'''","value":["The Back Porch"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Agassiz"]]},".  A further list of potters are open by appointment. Call the studios to confirm they will be open."]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Stay safe"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["outlineregion"]]},"\n\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["geo"],["49.108333"],["-122.291667"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["IsPartOf"],["Lower Mainland"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["WikiPedia:Fraser_Valley"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Dmoz:Regional\/North_America\/Canada\/British_Columbia\/Regional_Districts\/Fraser_Valley"]]}]